sh thingies. I had to fight 3 bad guys at once last night, and managed to take out the mage in the back with 2 poison arrows before the 2 fighters reached me. I still miss a lot more than I hit though. <br><br>Here's one tip I read that's really helped me work around my lack of Speechcraft. As soon as I could I joined the Mage Guild to get access to their spellmaker. Then I made a spell that boosts my personality by 40 points for 3 seconds - just long enough to cast it and initiate a conversation. It saves me a few bucks when dealing with merchants, but more importantly, it makes provoking Bad People into fights much easier. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>I'm starting to think this is a pretty big game. Huge, actually. I ran from Caldera to Gnar Mok last night, which look pretty close on the map, and it was a pretty good run. Just staying on the road, I passed a mine, a tomb, and a shipwreck off the coast that will need to be explored at some point. There's all kinds of tombs and ruins in the wilderness too. I'm betting you could play for weeks and still not see or do everything. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 5/6/02 6:08:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ucreepypete.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CreepyPete</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ligh